### Archivo de pruebas HTTP para endpoints de órdenes
### Reemplaza {{BACKEND_URL}} con tu URL de Render (ej: https://tu-backend.onrender.com/api)

### 1. Health Check
GET {{BACKEND_URL}}/health

### 2. Obtener todas las órdenes
GET {{BACKEND_URL}}/admin/orders

### 3. Obtener órdenes con filtros
GET {{BACKEND_URL}}/admin/orders?status=PENDING
GET {{BACKEND_URL}}/admin/orders?status=PAID
GET {{BACKEND_URL}}/admin/orders?raffleId=tu-raffle-id

### 4. Obtener orden específica por ID
GET {{BACKEND_URL}}/admin/orders/{{ORDER_ID}}

### 5. Marcar orden como pagada
PUT {{BACKEND_URL}}/admin/orders/{{ORDER_ID}}/mark-paid
Content-Type: application/json

### 6. Editar orden (cliente, boletos, notas)
PUT {{BACKEND_URL}}/admin/orders/{{ORDER_ID}}/edit
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer": {
    "name": "Juan Pérez",
    "phone": "5551234567",
    "email": "juan@email.com",
    "district": "Centro"
  },
  "tickets": [1, 2, 3],
  "notes": "Cliente VIP"
}

### 7. Liberar orden (devolver boletos al inventario)
PUT {{BACKEND_URL}}/admin/orders/{{ORDER_ID}}/release
Content-Type: application/json

### 8. Actualizar orden (método genérico)
PATCH {{BACKEND_URL}}/admin/orders/{{ORDER_ID}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "PAID",
  "notes": "Pago confirmado"
}

### 9. Eliminar orden
DELETE {{BACKEND_URL}}/admin/orders/{{ORDER_ID}}

### Variables de ejemplo:
# BACKEND_URL = https://tu-backend.onrender.com/api
# ORDER_ID = uuid-de-la-orden
